data.content:
noun
plural ~ -ings
[count] :a landing in which an airplane, a spacecraft, etc., touches the ground in a controlled and gradual way that does not damage it
The lunar module made a soft landing on the moon. - often used figuratively to describe an ending or solution that is not difficult or harmful
Market analysts are predicting a soft landing for the economy after the economic boom.

Danh từ
sự hạ cánh an toàn (của con tàu vũ trụ xuống trái đất, mặt trăng…)
